# What goals do CCL schools have?

Guiding question: **Which of these goals best describe your reason for innovating? Select up to 3.**

CCL schools are primarily prioritizing increasing student agency, with nearly 70% selecting it as their key goal for engaging in innovative work. Nearly half are motivated by the opportunity to demonstrate what's possible, and 1 in 5 is aiming to improve academics.  

```{r}
# n/pct of goals
ccl_goals <- ccl %>% 
  select(school_id, starts_with("catalyst")) %>% 
  select(-c(catalyst_key_other, catalyst_key_other_text), -starts_with("catalyst_key_support_")) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = -school_id,
               names_to = "variable",
               values_to = "selection") %>% 
  left_join(labs, by = "variable") %>% 
  group_by(short_label) %>% 
  summarize(n = sum(selection),
            total = n_distinct(school_id),
            pct = n/total) 
# create plot
ccl_goals_plot <- 
  ccl_goals %>% 
  ggplot(., aes(pct, reorder(short_label, pct))) +
    geom_col(fill = "#004B72") +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0,0),
                       limits = c(0, 1.05),
                       labels = scales::label_percent()) +
    theme_bw() +
    labs(x = "Percent of CCL schools",
         y = "") +
    theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 12),
          panel.grid.major.y = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank()) +
    geom_text(aes(label = scales::number(pct * 100, accuracy = 1)),
              hjust = 1.2,
              color = "white",
              size = 5)
ccl_goals_plot
```

