# What outcomes are CCL schools prioritizing and measuring? [i.e., how do they know if they're successful?]

Guiding question: **How important are the following student outcomes in your school’s CCL approach?**

It's a little difficult to get labels into this plot given most schools did not select any of the listed outcomes as not important. However, there are a few pieces here that really stand out:  
- 8 of the 96 CCL schools indicated that industry credentials are "Not important" while another 20 indicated they are "Somewhat not important"  
- 13 of the 96 CCL schools indicated that social capital is "Not important" (1) or "Somewhat not important" (12)  
- Nearly all (93% or 89) indicated that engagement is "Very important" - standing out as a clear priority for CCL schools  
- Belonging (90%) and durable skills (89%) were also at the top of the "Very important" list  
- No schools indicated that engagement, agency and self-direction, identity and purpose, or durable skills are "Not important" or "Somewhat not important"  

```{r}
# n/pct of goals
ccl_outcomes <- ccl %>% 
  select(school_id, starts_with("ccl_outcome")) %>% 
  select(-ends_with("measure")) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = -school_id,
               names_to = "variable",
               values_to = "selection") %>% 
  mutate(rate = 1) %>% 
  left_join(labs, by = "variable") %>% 
  filter(!is.na(selection)) %>% 
  group_by(short_label, selection) %>% 
  summarize(n = sum(rate), .groups = "drop") %>% 
  group_by(short_label) %>% 
  mutate(total = sum(n),
         pct = n/total) %>% 
  mutate(selection = factor(selection, levels = c("Not important", "Somewhat not important", "Somewhat important", "Very important")))
# create plot
ccl_outcomes_plot <- 
  ccl_outcomes %>% 
  ggplot(., aes(pct, reorder(short_label, pct), fill = selection)) +
    geom_bar(position = "stack", stat = "identity") +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("#F2AD4B", "#F9DAAF", "#0178BA", "#004B72")) +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0,0),
                       limits = c(0, 1),
                       labels = scales::label_percent()) +
    scale_y_discrete(labels = function(x) stringr::str_wrap(x, width = 30)) +
    theme_bw() +
    labs(x = "Percent of CCL schools",
         y = "",
         fill = "") +
    theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 11),
          panel.grid.major.y = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
          legend.position = "top",
          legend.text = element_text(size = 8)) +
    guides(fill = guide_legend(reverse = TRUE)) 
