# What gets in the way of measuring progress toward their goals? [i.e., barriers and enablers]

Guiding question: **What are the biggest barriers your school faces when measuring progress toward the outcomes you care about?**

Two clear barriers stand out: over half of CCL schools cited that collecting data (51%) and having the capacity to regularly use that data (52%) are the biggest barriers their school faces when measuring progress. A quarter (26%) also reported they're unsure what assessments or measures to use.  

```{r}
# n/pct
barriers <- ccl %>% 
  select(school_id, starts_with("ccl_barrier")) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = -school_id,
               names_to = "variable",
               values_to = "selection") %>% 
  left_join(labs, by = "variable") %>% 
  group_by(full_label) %>% 
  summarize(n = sum(selection),
            total = n_distinct(school_id),
            pct = n/total) 
# create plot
barriers_plot <- 
  barriers %>% 
  ggplot(., aes(pct, reorder(full_label, pct))) +
    geom_col(fill = "#004B72") +
    scale_x_continuous(expand = c(0,0),
                       limits = c(0, 1.05),
                       labels = scales::label_percent()) +
    scale_y_discrete(labels = function(x) stringr::str_wrap(x, width = 45)) +
    theme_bw() +
    labs(x = "Percent of CCL schools",
         y = "") +
    theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 12),
          panel.grid.major.y = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor.y = element_blank(),
          panel.grid.minor.x = element_blank()) +
    geom_text(aes(label = scales::number(pct * 100, accuracy = 1)),
              hjust = -.1,
              color = "black",
              size = 5)
barriers_plot
